1) No one would measure the biggest economy in the world based on the amount its grown. So, I felt no need to explain because as one who understands world finance, I understand the economic pictures and how these things are measured.  I didnt remember to step it down a few levels for someone who, even though they know the truth, would try to play a game of semantics.  Proving my point in one message would also be no fun because then I wouldnt be able to keep poking at you. In fact, everyone else seemed to understand my meaning but you...what does that say about your intellect?<br>
<br>
2) The USA existing in 1776 has no direct comparison to the EU. They are so phenomenally different in structure, beliefs, intent, and control that you are grasping at straw men.  You are trying to use a different historical context in a conversation that was simply about the fact that until France can take up what the USA offers for the world and find a way to make us minorly important without hurting themselves and the world in the process, they are welcome to try. I never suggested it be a military intervention. I suggested they remember how to be a superpower and find a way to take up the humanitarian, military, and economic duties we perform so they can do something about it.  You knew that, but again, I know you like to nitpick over stuff you clearly understood the meaning of. <br>
BUT SINCE YOU INSIST... The confederacy, even in 1776, had centralized powers of military (they just werent supporting it well), foreign policy (they had a 3 man committee), and regulatory powers (in 1776 they created the ability to be able to gather funds for the military and controls on interstate commerce).  The EU does not have that. <br>
<br>
3) I never said a soverign nation is one that can effect another.  I said a soveriegn nation has powers of foreign policy (this is a key power), military (key one again), and broad regulatory controls (not limited).  <br>
<br>
4) If you read my posts in here and other places (cant remember but think this thread), I have even stated China, Germany, and Britain are the ones I would consider main powers in the world besides us that can make broad differences. Germany is one of the most powerful economies and really is a huge backbone to the EU (thats why France buddy buddied them to create the EU).  China has a huge military and is headed on its way to a great economy with capitalist influence, Britain is one of the greatest foreign policy powers with some of the greatest access to foreign information in the world, and then we are who we are.  If Britain and Germany get on the same page, they will more then likely be what truly carries the EU forward.  Japan is becoming more and more of an economic sidenote, but still has the ability to get in world prominence through their massive amount of foreign investment. <br>
<br>
BUT MY POINT WAS, again, that any country who is busy whining and bitching really does not have much they can do about it until they can find a way to no longer let us be the biggest player in the world economy, world policing, and humanitarian effort.  I will be happy to let our economy, military, and humanitarian aid to be our own but not at the sacrifice of someone not handling what needs to be done.<br>
Until that time, they can whine and moan all they want, but our power is number one and remains unchecked because the world needs us very badly.  <br>
<br>
That is a fact. <br>
